    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You chant steadily while holding either a jeweled ear horn to your ear or a clear quartz eye in front of your own eye. Mentally imagining the sounds or sights of a nearby place, you start to hear sounds from the horn or see things through the eye, finally seeing and hearing as if you were in the chosen location.</em></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><strong>Materials:</strong> <span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You require a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.FLNifyCCwr9yVoLz]{clear quartz eye} or a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.mIhr5SfoDYAHTVme]{jeweled horn}, typically valued at 100 gold.</span></p></div><p class=\"MsoBodyText\"><strong>Summoning Spell</strong></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">You create an invisible sensor within range in a location familiar to you (a place you have visited or seen before) or in an obvious location that is unfamiliar to you (such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a grove of trees). You don't need line of sight to the target.</p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">The sensor is a tiny construct. It cannot move or take actions.</p></li><li><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">You can see and hear through the sensor.</p></li><li><p>A creature that can see the sensor (such as a creature benefiting from <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.Wp9ckwdiUpIuPE5l]{See Invisibility} </em>or &amp;reference[truesight]) sees a luminous, intangible orb about the size of your fist.</p></li><li><p>The sensor is incorporeal and cannot be destroyed, but it can be covered or dispelled.</p></li></ul>",
            "chat": "<p><strong>Materials:</strong> <span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You require a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.FLNifyCCwr9yVoLz]{clear quartz eye} or a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.mIhr5SfoDYAHTVme]{jeweled horn}, typically valued at 100 gold.</span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\"><strong>Summoning Spell</strong></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">You create an invisible sensor within range in a location familiar to you (a place you have visited or seen before) or in an obvious location that is unfamiliar to you (such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a grove of trees). You don't need line of sight to the target.</p><ul><li><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">The sensor is a tiny construct. It cannot move or take actions.</p></li><li><p class=\"MsoBodyText\">You can see and hear through the sensor.</p></li><li><p>A creature that can see the sensor (such as a creature benefiting from <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.Wp9ckwdiUpIuPE5l]{See Invisibility} </em>or &amp;reference[truesight]) sees a luminous, intangible orb about the size of your fist.</p></li><li><p>The sensor is incorporeal and cannot be destroyed, but it can be covered or dispelled.</p></li></ul>"
